<article class="daily-norm" aria-labelledby="daily-norm-title">
  <div class="daily-norm__top">
    <div class="daily-norm__icon" aria-hidden="true">
      <svg class="daily-norm__icon-svg" width="20" height="20">
        <use href="#icon-dumbbell"></use>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <div class="daily-norm__heading">
      <h3 class="daily-norm__title" id="daily-norm-title">110 min</h3>
      <p class="daily-norm__subtitle">Daily norm of sports</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p class="daily-norm__text">
    The World Health Organization recommends at least 150 minutes of
    moderate-intensity aerobic physical activity throughout the week for adults
    aged 18–64. However, what happens if we adjust that number to 110 minutes
    every day? While it might seem like a high number to hit, dedicating 110
    minutes daily to sporting activities may offer unparalleled benefits to
    physical health, mental well-being, and overall quality of life.
  </p>
</article>
